<br>
You could have a 500 damage nuke for 100 mana and still suck at nuking, since wizards could have a 2000 damge nuke for 600 and be 4x better because mana doesnt matter as much with bard song + Kei + FT + random effects + rods<br>
<br>
Im rather dissapointed at the fact that there used to be some kind of difference between Wizard - Mage - Druid - everyone else nuking<br>
<br>
Now its more like Wizard &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Druid &gt;&gt; Mage=Necro,Enchanter,Cleric,Shaman<br>
<br>
Since I alway assumed those non-nuking classes had other spells, you know like defensive and utility spells.  Necros now have a more or less equal nuke to us, chanters are getting 1100 pt and so are clerics.  That puts us at a severe disadvantage unless our nukes are *substaintally* better, which they arent<br>
<br>
What does this mean? Mod rods..it's that simple, if we cant prove we are good nukers then people will want our mana to nuke since they have 1100 pt nukes and we have 1300.. Which is a pretty small difference compared to our 1300 to 2700 pt wizard nuke, or even garrisons.. <br>
<br>
The balance of mage/druid nuking to wizard nuking compared to everyone else is getting insanely out of focus here.  Is verant scared to give the original nukers more power instead of simply wizards? I wont be as annoyed if our pets are uber, however I don't really have a lot of faith in that either<br>
<br>
Our place as a damage dealer might become very eroded in PoP by classes who have 10x more advantages than us, then gain the ability to nuke as well<br>
<br>
Druid *and* mage nukes should be about 400pts above Chanter/cleric/necro nukes, not 200.  Not only do necros have 2100 pt dots, but they have root, snare, fear, FD, succor, pets, DA, 1000 pt nukes, huge mana regen, group mana regen, group hp regen, lifetaps, I might of forgot an ability in there...<br>
<br>
The only 3 classes imo who should nuke well are Wizards, Druids and Mages.  Wizards should always have very much superior nukes as their role is quick damage (although its becoming sustained DPS now, to infringe on mages).  Druids should have slightly better nukes than mages and mages should have *good* ratio but low damage nukes in comparison to wizards, since ratios mean less and less now.  Our original job as mages was high sustained DPS, but with mana regen being so high now wizards now rule that category and we're left with a bunch of pop guns and some fire works...<br>
